==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sacchulmic
<hw>Sac*chul"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sacch</ets>arine + <ets>ulmic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid
obtained as a dark amorphous substance by the long-continued boiling of
sucrose with very dilute sulphuric acid. It resembles humic acid.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>sacculmic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sacchulmin</ent>⟦br⟧
